*after installed nodejs16 with npm8 and docker, docker-compose, mongo-client

    > ./nodesource_setup.sh //the setup script for nodejs-16

*Pull MongoDB image
    > docker pull mongo:latest
*cd Check image
    > docker images
*Create init-mongo.js setup user, passwd, db_name, role
*Create docker-compose.yml
*Run docker-compose.yml
    > docker-compose up -d
*mongo is work
*prepair node for work with mongo
    > mkdir mongotest
    > npm init --y
    > npm install --save mongodb
*in a folder stored files which are need for find insert create in mongo etc
  


